<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Boanerges on 01-23-2002 12:23 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">On the upside, Nagafen is out of the picture. Definitely a good change. There's also one more step to the quest now. Also a good change. And Wizards cna buy their imbue spell much more easily. Good there.

The problem I forsee is this...

As it reads right now, the agro version of Zordak spawns in Skyfire. He is UNTRIGGERED. Meaning any decent group can go kill him for their cleric IRREGARDLESS OF HAVING COMPLETED THE REST OF THE QUEST. Assuming that Zordallicus is unchanged from his SolB version, this spells disaster for the epic.

 [QUOTE]Posted by Arele Nyxx:
[b]What some of you describe happens on your servers is scary. Or maybe I'm just out of touch with that sort of thing..dunno.[/b][/QUOTE]

I honestly have no clue how things are on MM. Can only speak from experience on CT.

With a freestanding epic mob without prerequisites to get the epic piece I forsee everyone and their dog going to Skyfire and farming Zordak for each and every cleric that would potentially get an epic. This means that people who need this as their last step must now compete with the farmers for their epic.

I'd love nothing more than to believe that this will alleviate the problems that have made this epic the second worst to complete (mage is still worse) but I also have played this game too long and I know better. I have seen twink clerics get their epics over the heads of primaries whose guilds were a bit too slow. I have seen people train and KS each other this. And while these incidents have been gone for quite some time from CT I can't help but think this will bring them back. I also wonder what moron decided the second Zordak should be untriggered.

Of course, we don't know what will happen. I'd love nothing more to be wrong on this. I'd like to think this will make the cleric epic attainable for all who can do the other steps. But I also know Verant is shortsighted and players are often a greedy lot.

Only time will tell on this one...

------------------
Boanerges Thundercry
High Priest of Prexus
[URL=http://www.cohort.cc]Cohort Chalybeius[/URL]
Cazic Thule Server</TEXTAREA>
